message.content:
Apple pie:
- Overall Shape: Round pie, often in a shallow dish
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Sliced apple pieces, pastry crust
- Dominant Color: Golden brown crust, pale yellow to light brown apple filling
- Cooking Methods: Baked
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Lattice crust or solid top crust with vent slits; flaky pastry texture
- Cut or Layer Detail: Visible layers of cooked apple slices beneath crust, sometimes syrupy filling surrounding slices

Baby back ribs:
- Overall Shape: Curved rack of individual rib bones connected by meat
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Pork ribs, visible rib bones, barbecue sauce or glaze
- Dominant Color: Reddish-brown with darker char or glaze spots
- Cooking Methods: Grilled, smoked, or roasted
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Glazed, slightly caramelized surface with grill marks or bark
- Cut or Layer Detail: Meat closely fitted around bones, visible separation between ribs when cut

Baklava:
- Overall Shape: Rectangular or diamond-shaped pieces
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Thin phyllo dough layers, chopped nuts (walnuts, pistachios, or almonds)
- Dominant Color: Golden brown top, light tan layers inside
- Cooking Methods: Baked and soaked in syrup or honey
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Crisp, flaky top with visible nut pieces beneath
- Cut or Layer Detail: Multiple thin, distinct phyllo layers separated by nut filling

Beef carpaccio:  
- Overall Shape: Thin, circular slices arranged flat or slightly overlapping  
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Raw beef, olive oil drizzle, capers, shaved Parmesan, arugula or microgreens  
- Dominant Color: Deep red beef, white or pale yellow cheese, green garnish  
- Cooking Methods: Raw, thinly sliced  
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth, translucent beef slices with glossy oil sheen  
- Cut or Layer Detail: Very thin, almost paper-thin slices, uniformly cut

Beef tartare:
- Overall Shape: Roughly circular mound or patty
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Finely chopped raw beef, capers, onions, egg yolk sometimes on top
- Dominant Color: Bright red beef, occasional yellow from egg yolk, green from herbs or capers
- Cooking Methods: Raw, no cooking applied
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Coarse, uneven texture with visible small meat chunks
- Cut or Layer Detail: Uniformly minced or finely diced raw beef mixed with small ingredient pieces, no distinct layers

Beet salad:
- Overall Shape: Irregular, loosely piled or layered
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Cubed or sliced beets, leafy greens, crumbled cheese (feta or goat), nuts or seeds (optional)
- Dominant Color: Deep red or purple from beets, green from leaves, white from cheese
- Cooking Methods: Roasted or boiled beets, raw or lightly dressed greens
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Moist, slightly glossy beets with textured cheese crumbs and leafy textures
- Cut or Layer Detail: Uniform cubes or thin slices of beets, scattered cheese pieces, layered or mixed greens

Beignets:
- Overall Shape: Irregular square or rectangular puffs  
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Fried dough, powdered sugar coating  
- Dominant Color: Golden brown exterior, white powdery surface  
- Cooking Methods: Deep-fried  
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Puffy, slightly crisp edges, smooth to slightly uneven surface  
- Cut or Layer Detail: Hollow, airy interior with thin, crisp outer layer

Bibimbap:
- Overall Shape: Round bowl presentation
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Mixed rice, assorted vegetables (julienned cucumbers, carrots, spinach, bean sprouts), cooked ground meat or sliced beef, fried egg (sunny side up), gochujang (red chili paste) on top
- Dominant Color: Multicolored (green, orange, white, brown, red, yellow)
- Cooking Methods: Stir-fried or blanched vegetables, sautéed meat, fried egg, steamed rice
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Ingredients arranged in distinct, separated sections or clusters around the bowl with a central egg and sauce topping
- Cut or Layer Detail: Thin julienned or sliced vegetables, diced or ground meat, whole fried egg yolk visible

Bread pudding:  
- Overall Shape: Typically square or rectangular block or individual muffin-sized portions  
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Cubed bread pieces, custard-soaked  
- Dominant Color: Golden brown crust with pale to yellow custard interiors  
- Cooking Methods: Baked  
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Irregular, chunky bread cubes forming a mosaic-like surface  
- Cut or Layer Detail: Visible bread cubes saturated with custard, sometimes studded with raisins or nuts throughout

Breakfast burrito:
- Overall Shape: Cylindrical, tightly wrapped roll
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Flour tortilla, scrambled eggs, beans, cheese, potatoes, sausage or bacon
- Dominant Color: Light tan from tortilla with yellow (eggs), orange (cheese), and brown (meat/potatoes) accents
- Cooking Methods: Wrapped and lightly toasted or grilled
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth tortilla surface with occasional grill marks
- Cut or Layer Detail: Cross-section reveals layered fillings densely packed inside tortilla

Bruschetta:
- Overall Shape: Irregular oval or round slices  
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Toasted bread base, diced tomatoes, chopped basil, garlic, olive oil drizzle  
- Dominant Color: Light golden brown bread, bright red tomatoes, green basil  
- Cooking Methods: Grilled or toasted bread, fresh uncooked toppings  
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Crisp, porous toasted bread surface with chunky, moist tomato topping  
- Cut or Layer Detail: Single slice with diced tomato topping spread evenly on top

Caesar salad:
- Overall Shape: Loose, irregular mound in a bowl or plate
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Romaine lettuce leaves, croutons, grated Parmesan cheese, creamy dressing
- Dominant Color: Various shades of green (lettuce), light beige (croutons), off-white (cheese and dressing)
- Cooking Methods: Raw (lettuce), toasted or baked (croutons)
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Chunky croutons scattered unevenly, leafy texture with dressing coating
- Cut or Layer Detail: Large, torn or chopped lettuce leaves; small cubed or irregular croutons; finely grated cheese sprinkled on top

Cannoli:
- Overall Shape: Hollow, cylindrical tubes
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Crisp pastry shell, creamy ricotta filling, often with chocolate chips or candied fruit
- Dominant Color: Light golden brown shell, creamy white filling
- Cooking Methods: Deep-fried pastry shell, filled after cooking
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Slightly bubbled and flaky pastry texture with a rigid tubular form
- Cut or Layer Detail: Open ends showing smooth, dense filling inside

Caprese salad:
- Overall Shape: Circular or slightly irregular stacked or overlapping slices
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Fresh tomato slices, fresh mozzarella slices, basil leaves
- Dominant Color: Red (tomato), white (mozzarella), green (basil)
- Cooking Methods: Raw, no cooking
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth, moist surfaces of tomato and cheese, with glossy basil leaves
- Cut or Layer Detail: Even, thin round slices of tomato and mozzarella, layered alternately or arranged side-by-side

Carrot cake:
- Overall Shape: Round, square, or rectangular slices or whole cake
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Shredded carrot pieces, chopped nuts (often walnuts or pecans), cream cheese frosting
- Dominant Color: Light to medium brown or orange-brown cake, creamy white frosting
- Cooking Methods: Baked
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Slightly textured cake surface with visible carrot shreds and nut fragments; smooth or piped cream cheese frosting on top
- Cut or Layer Detail: Usually multiple layers with cream cheese frosting between and on top; visible carrot and nut speckles within cake layers

Ceviche:
- Overall Shape: Irregular, loosely piled chunks
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Raw fish or seafood pieces, diced onions, chili peppers, cilantro, lime wedges
- Dominant Color: Translucent white or pinkish fish, bright white onions, green herbs, red chili flecks
- Cooking Methods: Marinated (not cooked by heat)
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Wet, glistening with citrus juice, finely diced herbs and peppers interspersed
- Cut or Layer Detail: Small, irregular cubes or slices of fish mixed with thinly sliced onions and herbs

Cheesecake:
- Overall Shape: Round or square, often a single thick slice or whole cake
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Cream cheese filling, graham cracker or biscuit crust
- Dominant Color: Pale cream or off-white filling, light brown crust
- Cooking Methods: Baked or chilled (no-bake versions)
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth, glossy or matte top, sometimes with fruit toppings or glaze
- Cut or Layer Detail: Thick creamy layer above thin, crumbly crust layer

Cheese plate:
- Overall Shape: Assorted small blocks, wedges, or slices arranged on a flat platter
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Variety of cheese types (hard, soft, blue, aged), crackers or bread, sometimes fruits or nuts
- Dominant Color: Creamy whites, yellows, light oranges, occasional blues or greens (from mold)
- Cooking Methods: None, served cold or room temperature
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth, crumbly, or veined cheese surfaces; sometimes rind visible
- Cut or Layer Detail: Varied shapes—triangular wedges, rectangular blocks, thin slices, irregular chunks

Chicken curry:
- Overall Shape: Chunky pieces in a semi-liquid base
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Chicken chunks, curry sauce, visible spices or herbs
- Dominant Color: Yellow-orange to brownish hues
- Cooking Methods: Simmered or stewed
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Oily, glossy surface with visible spice granules or herbs
- Cut or Layer Detail: Irregular chicken pieces, sometimes shredded or bone-in

Chicken quesadilla:
- Overall Shape: Semi-circular or triangular wedge
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Grilled chicken pieces, melted cheese, folded flour tortilla
- Dominant Color: Golden brown tortilla, white or yellow cheese, light brown chicken
- Cooking Methods: Grilled or pan-fried
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Slightly crisp, browned tortilla surface with occasional grill marks
- Cut or Layer Detail: Visible layers showing chicken and melted cheese inside folded tortilla

Chicken wings:
- Overall Shape: Small, elongated pieces with tapered ends and a thicker meaty portion
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Skin-covered chicken wing segments (drumette and wingette/flat)
- Dominant Color: Golden brown to reddish-orange (depending on sauce or seasoning)
- Cooking Methods: Fried, baked, or grilled
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Slightly crispy skin, often shiny or glazed with sauce
- Cut or Layer Detail: Whole small wings or separated into drumettes and flats; visible bone ends

Chocolate cake:
- Overall Shape: Typically round or square cake, whole or sliced
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Dark brown chocolate sponge, chocolate frosting or ganache
- Dominant Color: Deep dark brown to nearly black
- Cooking Methods: Baked
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth or slightly glossy frosting, sometimes textured with piping or crumbs
- Cut or Layer Detail: Multiple layers of chocolate cake separated by chocolate or cream filling, clearly visible dark layers

Chocolate mousse:
- Overall Shape: Typically served in a small bowl or glass, mound-like or softly domed
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Whipped chocolate mixture, sometimes topped with whipped cream or chocolate shavings
- Dominant Color: Dark brown to medium brown
- Cooking Methods: Chilled, aerated (whipped)
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Light, airy texture with slight peaks or smooth glossy surface
- Cut or Layer Detail: No distinct layers; uniformly smooth or fluffy throughout

Churros:
- Overall Shape: Long, cylindrical sticks, often straight or slightly curved
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Fried dough exterior, sometimes accompanied by sugar coating or dipping sauce
- Dominant Color: Golden brown
- Cooking Methods: Deep-fried
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Ridged or fluted texture running lengthwise
- Cut or Layer Detail: Solid dough interior without distinct layers

Clam chowder:
- Overall Shape: Thick, creamy soup with a slightly chunky consistency
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Clam pieces, diced potatoes, onions, celery, sometimes bacon bits
- Dominant Color: Off-white to pale beige, creamy appearance
- Cooking Methods: Simmered, stewed
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Opaque, creamy broth with floating solid ingredients
- Cut or Layer Detail: Small, irregularly shaped clam and potato chunks dispersed throughout

Club sandwich:
- Overall Shape: Rectangular or square, stacked triple-layered
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Toasted white bread, sliced turkey or chicken, bacon strips, lettuce, tomato slices, mayonnaise
- Dominant Color: Light golden-brown bread, green lettuce, red tomato, pale meat, reddish-brown bacon
- Cooking Methods: Toasted bread, cooked bacon
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Grilled bread surface with slight browning and crisp edges
- Cut or Layer Detail: Diagonal cut revealing three distinct bread layers separated by meat, bacon, lettuce, and tomato layers

Crab cakes:
- Overall Shape: Thick, round patties
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Lump crab meat, breadcrumbs, finely chopped herbs or vegetables (e.g., green onions, bell peppers)
- Dominant Color: Golden brown exterior, light beige crab meat interior
- Cooking Methods: Pan-fried or baked
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Crispy, slightly uneven textured crust with visible bits of crab and herbs
- Cut or Layer Detail: Flaky interior with discernible chunks of crab meat, moist and tender inside

Creme brulee:
- Overall Shape: Typically round, shallow ramekin or custard cup
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Caramelized sugar crust, creamy custard base
- Dominant Color: Golden brown caramelized top, pale yellow custard beneath
- Cooking Methods: Baked custard, torch caramelized sugar topping
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Even, glossy, crackly caramelized sugar layer on top
- Cut or Layer Detail: Smooth, uniform custard layer beneath brittle caramel top, no distinct layers within custard

Croque madame:
- Overall Shape: Rectangular toasted sandwich
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Ham, melted cheese, fried egg on top
- Dominant Color: Golden brown toast, yellow yolk, white egg whites, pale ham, light melted cheese
- Cooking Methods: Grilled or toasted sandwich, fried egg sunny-side up
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Crispy toasted bread edges, smooth melted cheese layer, glossy fried egg yolk on top
- Cut or Layer Detail: Visible sandwich layers of bread, ham, and cheese; fried egg placed whole on top without slicing

Cup cakes:
- Overall Shape: Small, individual, cylindrical with flared top
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Sponge cake base, piped frosting or icing on top
- Dominant Color: Varied; often pastel or bright frosting with beige or brown cake base
- Cooking Methods: Baked
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Swirled or peaked frosting, sometimes decorated with sprinkles or small toppings
- Cut or Layer Detail: Single cake layer with thick frosting layer on top; usually no internal layers visible

Deviled eggs:
- Overall Shape: Halved oval egg whites
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Hard-boiled egg white halves filled with creamy yolk mixture
- Dominant Color: White egg white, bright yellow to pale yellow filling
- Cooking Methods: Boiled eggs, mixed filling
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth, piped or spooned filling with occasional sprinkled paprika or herbs
- Cut or Layer Detail: Clean halved eggs revealing distinct white outer layer and yolk-based filling center

Donuts:
- Overall Shape: Ring-shaped or round whole pieces, occasional filled rounds without holes  
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Fried dough, sugar glaze, icing, sprinkles, or powdered sugar  
- Dominant Color: Golden brown base with vibrant icing colors (white, pink, chocolate, etc.)  
- Cooking Methods: Deep-fried  
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth or glossy glazed surface, sometimes with sprinkled toppings or drizzled icing  
- Cut or Layer Detail: Typically solid dough interior, sometimes filled with jelly or cream, no layered structure

Dumplings:
- Overall Shape: Crescent, half-moon, round, or pleated pouch
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Thin dough wrapper, visible filling through slight translucency or open ends in some styles
- Dominant Color: Pale off-white to light beige dough; filling varies (meat, vegetable tones visible if exposed)
- Cooking Methods: Steamed, boiled, pan-fried, or deep-fried
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth or pleated edges; sometimes browned or crispy on fried side
- Cut or Layer Detail: Generally whole pocket; cut dumplings show dense filling tightly encased by thin dough layer

Edamame:  
- Overall Shape: Small, elongated pods  
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Soybean pods with visible beans inside  
- Dominant Color: Bright to dark green  
- Cooking Methods: Boiled or steamed, sometimes lightly salted  
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth pods with subtle longitudinal ridges  
- Cut or Layer Detail: Usually whole pods, occasionally showing split pod edges or exposed beans inside

Eggs benedict:
- Overall Shape: Oval or round stacked components
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Poached eggs, English muffin halves, Canadian bacon or ham, hollandaise sauce
- Dominant Color: Pale yellow (hollandaise and egg yolk), light beige (muffin), pinkish (ham)
- Cooking Methods: Poached eggs, toasted muffin, lightly cooked ham, sauce poured
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth, glossy hollandaise coating, soft poached egg whites visible
- Cut or Layer Detail: Layers from bottom to top: English muffin, ham, poached egg, hollandaise sauce draped over edges

Escargots:
- Overall Shape: Small, rounded shell-like portions arranged in a circular pattern
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Snail meat tucked inside shells, garlic herb butter
- Dominant Color: Glossy greenish-yellow (garlic butter), brown or beige shell edges
- Cooking Methods: Baked or broiled in shell
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Shiny, bubbling butter with finely chopped parsley or herbs on top
- Cut or Layer Detail: No cut layers; snail meat visible inside shell opening, often partially submerged in butter

Falafel:
- Overall Shape: Small, round or slightly flattened balls
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Ground chickpeas or fava beans, visible herbs (parsley, cilantro)
- Dominant Color: Golden brown exterior, green flecks inside
- Cooking Methods: Deep-fried or pan-fried
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Rough, coarse texture with crispy outer crust
- Cut or Layer Detail: Dense, crumbly interior with a greenish tint from herbs

Filet mignon:
- Overall Shape: Thick, round, cylindrical medallion
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Center-cut beef tenderloin steak
- Dominant Color: Deep reddish-pink interior, light brown seared exterior
- Cooking Methods: Pan-seared, grilled, or broiled
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Uniform sear with slight crust, minimal marbling
- Cut or Layer Detail: Solid single muscle cut, no visible layers or fat marbling inside

Fish and chips:
- Overall Shape: Irregular elongated pieces (fish) with cluster of rectangular or wedge-shaped fries
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Battered fried fish fillets, thick-cut fried potato chips
- Dominant Color: Golden brown (fish batter and chips)
- Cooking Methods: Deep-fried
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Crispy, bubbled batter texture on fish; rough, porous surface on fries
- Cut or Layer Detail: Fish fillets with flaky interior visible on broken edges; chunky, rectangular-cut potato pieces

Foie gras:
- Overall Shape: Oval or rectangular block, sometimes molded
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Duck or goose liver pâté, occasionally served with garnish or fruit compote
- Dominant Color: Rich beige to pale pinkish-brown
- Cooking Methods: Seared, baked, or terrine (poached and chilled)
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth, glossy surface if seared; marbled or uniform if terrine
- Cut or Layer Detail: Thick slices with smooth, dense texture; sometimes visible fat marbling or layered with inclusions like truffles

French fries:
- Overall Shape: Long, narrow sticks or strips
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Potato pieces
- Dominant Color: Golden yellow to light brown
- Cooking Methods: Deep-fried or oven-baked
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Crispy, slightly rough exterior with occasional bubbles or blisters
- Cut or Layer Detail: Uniform rectangular or slightly irregular cross-section, smooth cut surfaces

French onion soup:
- Overall Shape: Bowl of liquid with floating toppings
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Caramelized onions, toasted bread slice, melted cheese
- Dominant Color: Golden brown broth, light to dark brown onions, creamy yellow to golden cheese
- Cooking Methods: Simmered broth, caramelized onions, broiled or baked melted cheese on bread
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Layer of bubbly, browned melted cheese covering bread floating on liquid
- Cut or Layer Detail: Bread slice submerged partially or fully under melted cheese layer, thin onion strands visible in broth

French toast:  
- Overall Shape: Thick rectangular or triangular slices  
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Egg-soaked bread, powdered sugar, syrup drizzle, occasional fruit garnish  
- Dominant Color: Golden brown with lighter interior  
- Cooking Methods: Pan-fried or griddled  
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Slightly crisp, unevenly browned surface with small bubbles or crust edges  
- Cut or Layer Detail: Single thick slice, sometimes stacked or overlapped, showing soft interior texture

Fried calamari:
- Overall Shape: Irregular rings and tentacle clusters
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Battered squid pieces, visible squid texture beneath batter
- Dominant Color: Golden brown exterior
- Cooking Methods: Deep-fried
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Crispy, rough, and bubbly textured coating
- Cut or Layer Detail: Hollow circular cross-sections for rings, twig-like shapes for tentacles

Fried rice:  
- Overall Shape: Loose, grainy mound or scattered heap  
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Cooked rice grains, diced vegetables (carrots, peas), scrambled egg pieces, small meat or seafood bits (optional)  
- Dominant Color: Light golden or brownish from soy sauce and frying, mixed with colorful vegetable bits  
- Cooking Methods: Stir-fried in a pan or wok  
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Individual separated grains with slight glisten, uneven texture due to mixed ingredients  
- Cut or Layer Detail: No layers, random distribution of small diced ingredients mixed thoroughly with rice grains

Frozen yogurt:
- Overall Shape: Soft-serve swirl or scoop shapes
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Smooth creamy yogurt base, occasional fruit or topping garnishes
- Dominant Color: White or pale cream, sometimes pastel hues from fruit or flavoring
- Cooking Methods: Frozen, churned but not baked
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth, glossy surface with subtle ridges from swirling or scooping
- Cut or Layer Detail: Typically no layers; uniform creamy texture throughout

Garlic bread:
- Overall Shape: Long, rectangular or oval loaf slices
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Bread, visible minced or sliced garlic, melted butter or oil
- Dominant Color: Golden brown crust, pale yellow to light brown topping
- Cooking Methods: Baked or toasted
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Crispy, slightly bubbly or blistered surface with specks of garlic and herbs
- Cut or Layer Detail: Sliced cross-sections showing soft crumb inside with toasted edges

Gnocchi:  
- Overall Shape: Small, rounded or oval dumplings  
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Potato or flour-based dough, sometimes with visible specks of herb or cheese  
- Dominant Color: Pale cream to off-white  
- Cooking Methods: Boiled, sometimes lightly pan-fried or baked after boiling  
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Soft, often with subtle ridges or grooves (from fork or gnocchi board)  
- Cut or Layer Detail: Uniform, bite-sized pieces without layers or fillings

Greek salad:
- Overall Shape: Irregular, chunky mix in a bowl or plate
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Large tomato wedges, thick cucumber slices, green bell pepper strips, whole or sliced Kalamata olives, large blocks or chunks of white feta cheese, red onion rings
- Dominant Color: Red (tomatoes), green (cucumber, peppers), white (feta), purple (onion), black (olives)
- Cooking Methods: Raw, no cooking
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Juicy, fresh vegetable textures, crumbly feta surface, glossy olive skins
- Cut or Layer Detail: Rough, chunky cuts—wedges and thick slices, feta in large cubes or slabs, onion in thin rings

Grilled cheese sandwich:  
- Overall Shape: Rectangular or square with rounded edges  
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Melted cheese between two slices of bread  
- Dominant Color: Golden brown crust, yellow or orange melted cheese  
- Cooking Methods: Pan-grilled or toasted  
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Evenly browned, crisp bread surface with occasional grill marks or slight bubbling  
- Cut or Layer Detail: Typically cut diagonally or in halves, showcasing melted cheese stretching or oozing between bread slices

Grilled salmon:
- Overall Shape: Rectangular or oval fillet pieces
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Salmon flesh, occasional lemon slice or herbs as garnish
- Dominant Color: Orange-pink flesh with darker grill marks
- Cooking Methods: Grilled with char lines
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Prominent parallel grill marks or sear lines
- Cut or Layer Detail: Visible distinct muscle fibers running lengthwise, slightly flaked edges from cooking

Guacamole:
- Overall Shape: Irregular, chunky mound or spread
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Mashed avocado, diced tomatoes, chopped onions, cilantro flecks, lime juice
- Dominant Color: Pale to medium green with red and white specks
- Cooking Methods: Raw, mashed and mixed
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Uneven, coarse texture with visible chunks and bits of ingredients
- Cut or Layer Detail: No distinct layers; mashed base with mixed-in pieces of vegetables and herbs

Gyoza:
- Overall Shape: Crescent-shaped, slightly plump half-moon
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Thin dough wrapper, visible pleats or folds on one side
- Dominant Color: Golden brown on one side, pale off-white on others
- Cooking Methods: Pan-fried bottom, steamed or boiled top
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Crispy, browned bottom with translucently soft, pleated upper surface
- Cut or Layer Detail: No internal layers visible; filling enclosed within dough wrapper

Hamburger:
- Overall Shape: Round, stacked sandwich
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Beef patty, sesame seed bun, lettuce, tomato, cheese, pickles, onions
- Dominant Color: Brown (patty), golden tan (bun), green (lettuce), red (tomato)
- Cooking Methods: Grilled or pan-fried patty, toasted bun
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Sesame seeds on top bun, grilled sear marks on patty
- Cut or Layer Detail: Visible layers of bun, patty, vegetables, and cheese separated distinctly

Hot and sour soup:
- Overall Shape: Broth-based, served in deep bowls
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Tofu cubes, thin wood ear mushrooms, shredded bamboo shoots, sliced mushrooms, egg ribbons
- Dominant Color: Dark brown or reddish broth with light-colored tofu and egg strands
- Cooking Methods: Boiled, simmered
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Swirling cloudiness from egg ribbons, floating tofu and mushroom pieces
- Cut or Layer Detail: Small, irregular tofu cubes, thinly sliced mushrooms and bamboo shoots, fine thread-like egg strands

Hot dog:
- Overall Shape: Cylindrical sausage within elongated bun
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Sausage, split hot dog bun, often mustard, ketchup, or relish
- Dominant Color: Light tan bun, reddish-brown sausage
- Cooking Methods: Grilled or boiled sausage, soft steamed or toasted bun
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth sausage surface with occasional grill marks; soft, slightly textured bun
- Cut or Layer Detail: Sausage fully enclosed or partially exposed by longitudinal bun split

Huevos rancheros:
- Overall Shape: Circular base with centered toppings
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Fried eggs, corn tortilla, salsa, refried beans, avocado slices, cilantro
- Dominant Color: Yellow yolk, red salsa, golden-brown tortilla
- Cooking Methods: Fried eggs sunny-side up, grilled or fried tortilla
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Runny or slightly set egg yolk atop salsa, tortilla edges slightly crisped
- Cut or Layer Detail: Single tortilla base with eggs and toppings layered on top, no slicing typically visible

Hummus:
- Overall Shape: Round shallow bowl or plate presentation
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Pureed chickpeas, olive oil drizzle, whole chickpeas, paprika or cumin sprinkle, parsley garnish
- Dominant Color: Pale beige to light tan
- Cooking Methods: Blended/pureed, no direct heat after blending
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth creamy surface with a swirl or dip in the center holding olive oil
- Cut or Layer Detail: Uniform smooth texture, no distinct layers or cuts

Ice cream:
- Overall Shape: Scooped or rounded dollops, sometimes in cones or cups
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Frozen dairy or non-dairy base, occasional mix-ins like chocolate chips or fruit bits
- Dominant Color: Varies widely; often pastel shades or creamy white tones
- Cooking Methods: Frozen, churned
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Smooth, creamy texture with occasional swirls or studded inclusions
- Cut or Layer Detail: Typically not layered, may show melting edges or drip trails

Lasagna:
- Overall Shape: Rectangular or square thick slices
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Pasta sheets, ground meat or vegetables, tomato sauce, cheese (mozzarella, ricotta)
- Dominant Color: Red (tomato sauce), beige (pasta), white/yellow (cheese)
- Cooking Methods: Baked
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Slightly browned, bubbly cheese layer on top
- Cut or Layer Detail: Multiple distinct, even layers of pasta, sauce, meat/vegetables, and cheese visible in cross-section

Lobster bisque:
- Overall Shape: Smooth, uniform soup in bowl or cup
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Finely pureed lobster meat, cream, sometimes whole lobster claw or meat pieces as garnish
- Dominant Color: Rich orange to reddish-brown
- Cooking Methods: Simmered, pureed, creamy finish
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Velvety smooth surface, sometimes lightly glazed with cream or oil
- Cut or Layer Detail: No layers, homogeneous texture with occasional chunky lobster pieces as garnish

Lobster roll sandwich:
- Overall Shape: Cylindrical or slightly oval sandwich, often handheld size
- Primary Visible Ingredients or Components: Lobster meat chunks or claw pieces, split-top hot dog bun
- Dominant Color: Bright red lobster meat contrasted with pale white or light golden bun
- Cooking Methods: Lobster meat usually boiled or steamed; bun lightly toasted or buttered
- Surface Pattern or Structure: Soft, split-top bun with visible lobster pieces spilling over or packed inside
- Cut or Layer Detail: Single bun sliced lengthwise, lobster loosely piled or mixed with light mayo or herbs inside
